| 3️⃣  | `else if ((ptr = file_path(...)), IS_ERR(ptr)) err = PTR_ERR(ptr);` – on error the function records the error code but does **not** copy any data to the user. | No data from an uninitialised area is exposed. |
| 4️⃣  | `else memmove(file->pathname, ptr, sizeof(file->pathname)-(ptr-file->pathname));` – copies a valid pathname into the zero‑initialised buffer. | The buffer is fully populated (or at least the part that will be visible to user space). |
